Class Piranha

  • java.lang.Object
    • itb.akadquarium.AquariumObject
      • itb.akadquarium.Piranha
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Fish

    public class Piranha
extends AquariumObject
implements Fish
    Class itb.akadquarium.Piranha. This class implements itb.akadquarium.Fish. itb.akadquarium.Piranha is an aquarium object than can be bought during the game using the coins that the player has. It also can drop coin directly after itb.akadquarium.Piranha eats itb.akadquarium.Guppy.

      • isHungry

        public boolean isHungry()
        This method checks whether itb.akadquarium.Piranha is hungry or not. Hungry is defined as if hunger is less than or equal to HUNGER_TIME.
        Returns:
        TRUE if itb.akadquarium.Piranha is hungry, otherwise FALSE

      • eat

        public void eat()
        This method will eat itb.akadquarium.Guppy. itb.akadquarium.Piranha only eats when itb.akadquarium.Piranha is hungry and will try to reach the nearest food available.
        Specified by:
        eat in interface Fish

      • dropCoin

        public void dropCoin()
        This method will drop coin. itb.akadquarium.Piranha will drop coin directly after eating. Also, coin value vary and be calculated as follows: GUPPY_PRICE multiply by STATE_OF_GUPPY added by one.
        Specified by:
        dropCoin in interface Fish

      • move

        public void move(java.awt.Graphics g)
        This method is used to move the object. itb.akadquarium.Piranha's movements are described as below: 1. If itb.akadquarium.Piranha is not hungry, itb.akadquarium.Piranha will move randomly. 2. If itb.akadquarium.Piranha is hungry and there is no food available, then it moves randomly. 3. If itb.akadquarium.Piranha is hungry and there is food available, then it moves towards the nearest food.
        Specified by:
        move in class AquariumObject
        Parameters:
        g - is Graphics
